In a press briefing at Morristown Municipal Airport, President Trump expressed his opinion on NFL players kneeling during the national anthem. He stated that he believes the owners should take action against the players, as he finds it disrespectful to the flag and the country. The President also mentioned his tax plan, stating that it is finalized and will be the largest tax cut in US history. He hopes to bring the corporate tax rate down to 15% and the individual rate to 10% or 12%. Additionally, he discussed the healthcare plan and expressed his frustration with the Republicans' inability to repeal and replace Obamacare. He believes that eventually, they will succeed in passing a new healthcare plan. The President also mentioned the travel ban, stating that he believes the tougher the restrictions, the better. The press briefing concluded at 4:31 P.M. EDT.